<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-12-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/248: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Coolidge</persName> to President <persName type="to">Guggiari</persName></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-12"><hi rend="italic">December 12,
                                        1928</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>I have received Your Excellency’s telegram of December 9 in relation
                                to the regrettable conflict that has taken place between Paraguay
                                and Bolivia and, in thanking Your Excellency for advising me
                                regarding this matter, I desire to express the most fervent hope
                                that the difficulty between your country and Bolivia will soon be
                                composed to the entire satisfaction of both parties.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Calvin
                                Coolidge</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>